{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/south_korea","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Tipping is <strong>not</strong> expected anywhere in South Korea and is not practiced by Koreans. It could be considered an insult between Koreans as it is regarded as giving someone charity, although people generally know of American tipping culture and would be understanding of a foreigner doing this.</p>\n<p>Many hotels and a few tourist restaurants add 10% service charge on their bills. Bellhops, hotel maids, taxi drivers and bars frequented by Westerners will not reject any tips that you care to hand out.</p>\n<p>Restaurants sometimes provide complimentary food or drinks to customers as a sign of generosity or to reward customer loyalty. Colloquially, this is known as \"service\".</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/south_korea","title":"South Korea","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-22","image":"south_korea.jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/90537/south_korea.jpg","srcSet":"/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/b3ebb/south_korea.jpg 270w,\n/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/95b54/south_korea.jpg 540w,\n/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/90537/south_korea.jpg 1080w,\n/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/3cda3/south_korea.jpg 1620w,\n/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/1f682/south_korea.jpg 2160w,\n/static/9a011c2ca4e926d0aa4b60b72453ad1f/0b354/south_korea.jpg 6000w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"south_korea.jpg"}}}